{
  "text": "We evaluated the hydrolytic stability of the most active compounds 3, 4, 8 and 9. NMR analysis of aqueous solutions (pH 2) of the compounds showed unchanged spectral characteristics after 30 days at room temperature. It is worth to note that, the class of compounds presented herein is considerably more stable than the widely studied phosphoramidates [CITATION_1] .",
